          "id": "ch1-mod1-p1",
          "title": "CIA triad: what security is trying to protect",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "Security is basically protecting three things: Confidentiality (keep secrets secret), Integrity (keep data accurate/unchanged), and Availability (keep systems usable when needed)."
            },
            {
              "type": "diagram",
              "text": "CIA =\nC: Who can SEE it?\nI: Who can CHANGE it?\nA: Can we USE it when needed?"
            },
            {
              "type": "example",
              "text": "Hospital records: C = only staff can view; I = records can't be tampered; A = doctors can access during emergencies."
            },
            {
              "type": "trap",
              "text": "If a service is down, that’s Availability. If data leaks, that’s Confidentiality. If data is modified, that’s Integrity."
            }
          ],
          "checks": [
            {
