        {
          "id": "ch1-mod1-p2",
          "title": "DAD triad: how attacks break CIA",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "DAD is the attacker’s version of CIA: Disclosure (data exposed), Alteration (data changed), Denial (access disrupted). Each maps directly to CIA."
            },
            {
              "type": "diagram",
              "text": "DAD -> CIA mapping:\nDisclosure -> Confidentiality\nAlteration -> Integrity\nDenial -> Availability"
            },
            {
              "type": "example",
              "text": "Data exfiltration = Disclosure. Website defacement = Alteration. DDoS = Denial."
            },
            {
              "type": "trap",
              "text": "CompTIA loves mapping questions: they describe an event in DAD language and ask which CIA principle is violated."
            }
          ],
          "checks": [
