          "id": "ch1-mod3-p2",
          "title": "DLP: stopping data exfiltration",
          "content_blocks": [
            {
              "type": "explain",
              "text": "Data Loss Prevention (DLP) enforces handling policies by finding sensitive data and blocking unauthorized movement (exfiltration)."
            },
            {
              "type": "diagram",
              "text": "DLP modes:\n- Agent-based (endpoint): scans storage + blocks actions (USB copy etc.)\n- Network-based (agentless): monitors outbound traffic for sensitive content"
            },
